public interface Trie<E,V>
extends Map<List<E>,V>, Serializable

Trie extends Map<List<E>,V> where keys are represented in a compact data structure (key sequences share common prefixes). Implementations may choose to support, null (or empty) key sequences and/or null values.

merge

void merge(Trie<? extends E,? extends V> source)
Merges source into this Trie. New nodes are created within this Trie as needed to encode all keys in source. For keys which are present in both Tries, the value present in source supersedes any existing value.

Parameters:
source -
